import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['adjclose'], label='Adjusted Close')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the stock prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['volume'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Volume')
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['volume'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Price')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['high'], label='High', color='green')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['low'], label='Low', color='red')
    ax.axhline(data['high'].max(), linestyle='--', color='green', label=f"Max High: {data['high'].max():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(data['low'].min(), linestyle='--', color='red', label=f"Min Low: {data['low'].min():.2f}")
    
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest price of the stock during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daily_return'] = data['adjclose'].pct_change()
    data = data.dropna()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['daily_return'], label='Daily Return', color='blue')
    avg_daily_return = data['daily_return'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_daily_return, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Daily Return: {avg_daily_return:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Daily Return')
    ax.set_title('What is the average daily return of the stock?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
